# View.elm — EARLY

HTML rendering primitives for a LynRummy board, hand, and
cards. Pure-drawing functions; no gesture handling here.

## Status

- **Label:** EARLY. Stable shape; expanding scope as new
  visual surfaces arrive (action buttons, score, etc.).

## Exposed surface

Constants:

- `navy` — `#000080`, the LynRummy spot color.
- `mergeableGreen` — light pastel green for mergeable wings.
- `mergeableHover` — `#E0B0FF` for cursor-over-wing state.
- `cardHeightPx` — `"40px"`.

Headings:

- `viewBoardHeading` — "Board" in bold navy.
- `viewHandHeading` — "Hand" in bold navy.

Board:

- `boardShell : List (Html msg) -> Html msg` — khaki play
  surface with navy border.
- `boardShellWith : List Attribute -> List (Html msg) -> Html msg`
  — same with extra attributes (id, mouseenter/leave).

Stack:

- `viewStack : CardStack -> Html msg` — render at its loc, no
  per-card hooks.
- `viewStackWithAttrs : List Attribute -> CardStack -> Html msg`
  — extra attributes on the stack div (e.g. opacity dim while
  dragging).
- `viewStackWithCardAttrs : (Int -> List Attribute) -> CardStack -> Html msg`
  — extra attributes on each card div, indexed by position.
  This is the hook the click-vs-drag inversion uses to put
  mousedown on cards instead of the parent stack.

Card:

- `viewCard : Card -> Html msg`
- `viewCardWithAttrs : List Attribute -> Card -> Html msg`

Hand:

- `viewHand : { attrsForCard : Int -> HandCard -> List Attribute } -> Hand -> Html msg`
  — renders the hand sorted into rows of 4 suits in display
  order (Heart / Spade / Diamond / Club), each row sorted by
  value ascending. Faithful to TS `PhysicalHand.populate`.

Wing:

- `viewWing : { top, left, width, bgColor, extraAttrs } -> Html msg`
  — board-level absolute sibling of the stack. Faithful port
  of `render_wing` (transparent +/+ chars for height) plus
  `style_as_mergeable` / `style_for_hover` colors at the call
  site.

## Architectural choices preserved across versions

- Wings render as **board-level siblings** of stacks, not
  inside the stack div. Avoids the TS pattern of "grow the
  wrapper and compensate by shifting the stack left," which
  Steve flagged as ugly in his own code. Stacks stay stable.
- Stack divs have no mousedown listener. Per-card mousedown
  via `viewStackWithCardAttrs` is the only entry point for
  board interaction. See `splitting_a_stack.md` for the
  rationale.

## Pointers

- Consumer: `Main.elm` composes the full view from these
  primitives.
- Depends on: `LynRummy.Card.cardColor` /
  `valueDisplayStr` / `suitEmojiStr`,
  `LynRummy.CardStack.incomplete`,
  `LynRummy.Hand`.
- TS reference: game.ts ~945-1180 (rendering primitives),
  ~1568-1602 (hand population).
